cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper focuses on parameterizations of database instances and queries to make query evaluation tractable. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper introduces a new Datalog fragment with stratified negation and discusses its evaluation on structures of bounded treewidth. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses fixed-parameter tractability of query evaluation and proves intractability results for probabilistic query evaluation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper uses tree automata and cycluits to evaluate queries on structures of bounded treewidth. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the evaluation of conjunctive queries and guarded negation fragment queries, which are commonly used in AI applications.
